The paper deals with planning algorithms for robotic spatial extrusion, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) in terms of collision detection and geometric constraints. Additionally, the paper deals with graphics (cs.GR) in terms of 3D printing and structures. The use of simulations and real-world applications involves multimedia (cs.MM) and control systems (cs.SY).
